  "comment_text": {
    "snp5.2:3.1": "The same verse was asked of Mahāvīra at Isibhāsiyāiṁ 29.1. The answers are quite different, however, as the Buddha directly addresses the question whereas Mahāvīra’s response is more oblique. ",
    "snp5.2:7.1": "“Appraised” is <i lang='pi' translate='no'>saṅkhāta</i>, literally “calculated, enumerated”. | <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Dhammāse</i> is an archaic masculine nominative plural found only in poetry (eg. <i lang='pi' translate='no'>sāvakāse</i> at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/dn21/en/sujato#1.12.11'>DN 21:1.12.11</a>, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>gatāse</i> at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn1.37/en/sujato#9.1'>SN 1.37:9.1</a>). "
  },
